  <body>
    <section name="SchemaCrawler - Velocity Example">
      <subsection name="Description">
        <p>The command example demonstrates the integration of SchemaCrawler
          with Apache
          Jakarta Velocity.
        </p>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="How to Run">
        <ol>
          <li>
            Install
            <a href="http://ant.apache.org/">ant,</a>
            and make sure that ant is on your
            path
          </li>
          <li>
            Make sure that
            <span class="code">java</span>
            is on your
            <span class="code">PATH</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            Start the database server by running the
            <span class="code">StartDatabaseServer</span>
            script from the
            distribution directory
          </li>
          <li>
            Start a command shell in the
            <span class="code">velocity</span>
            example directory
          </li>
          <li>
            Run
            <span class="code">velocity.cmd</span>
            (or
            <span class="code">velocity.sh</span>
            on Unix)
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="How to Experiment">
        <ol>
          <li>
            Try modifying the Velocity template,
            <span class="code">tables.vm</span>
            to modify the output produced.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>
